canonical_structure.name: UBX-AID-AOP
canonical_structure.description: AssistNow Autonomous data. If enabled, this message is output at irregular intervals. It is output whenever AssistNow Autonomous has produced new data for a satellite. It can also be sent in response to a poll request.

adjudication.reasoning: The extraction provided for the UBX-AID-AOP message matches the official u-blox 8 protocol specification exactly. The AID class (0x0B) message 0x33 is defined as a 68-byte payload containing the GNSS/SV identifiers and 64 bytes of autonomous orbit prediction data. While newer u-blox generations (M9+) transition to the MGA-AOP message, for the AID class, this structure is canonical.
